Takes specific frame from the specific skeleton data and shows in
Matlab 3D figure.

<Requires>
1) Matlab (tested on R2010a and above)

<Usage>
1) launch Matlab
2) run by "visualizeSkeleton('SKELETON_FILE_NAME',FRAME_NUM)"
    - replace SKELETON_FILE_NAME with skeleton data file
    - replace FRAME_NUM with frame number you wish to visualize

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This code is released as part of the Human Activity Detection project at Cornell University.
Refer to the website for more details about the project.
(http://pr.cs.cornell.edu/humanactivities/)
